{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3509", "repo": "rails", "body": "I don't know. I don't use Pry for Rails projects. If Pry wants to support Rails, maybe they aught to do something better than [this](https://gist.github.com/941174) (this insane script is linked from the readme. I don't think they're serious so far).\r\n\r\nAnyway, if you think Rails should be flexible enough so that users can choose their own console backend, probably I should better not directly monkey patch `IRB::ExtendCommandBundle` but create a new module defining `app`, `helpers` etc. and mix it into `IRB::ExtendCommandBundle`.\r\nIf you prefer that way, I'll make another patch.", "_id": {"$oid": "52383599bd3543c15100fc67"}, "issue_id": 3509, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2637212", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3509#issuecomment-2637212", "updated_at": "2011-11-04T22:15:21Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda", "login": "amatsuda", "gravatar_id": "76a777ff80f30bd3b390e275cce625bc", "html_url": "https://github.com/amatsuda", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/76a777ff80f30bd3b390e275cce625bc?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F76cac4685e3749728f9c04bd3a86221f.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 11493, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-11-04T22:15:21Z", "id": 2